  "The Doppler Effect The change in observed frequency (and wavelength) due to relative motion between a source and observer. The other options — 'Change in amplitude due to distance', 'Change in wavelength due to temperature', and 'Change in speed of sound' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": "",
  "If a sound source approaches, pitch:": "",
